  END IF;

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

begin
  qms$event_form('KEY-HELP','AFTER');
end;

/* CGYR$SET_DATE_FORMAT */
BEGIN
  set_application_property(DATE_FORMAT_COMPATIBILITY_MODE, '5.0');
  set_application_property(PLSQL_DATE_FORMAT, 'YYYY/MM/DD HH24:MI:SS');
  set_application_property(BUILTIN_DATE_FORMAT, 'YYYY/MM/DD HH24:MI:SS');
  forms_ddl('ALTER SESSION SET NLS_DATE_FORMAT = ''YYYY/MM/DD HH24:MI:SS''');
END;

/* CGNV$PRE_FORM_NAVCUR */
  DECLARE
  rg_id RECORDGROUP;
  gc_wnd GROUPCOLUMN;
  gc_item GROUPCOLUMN;
BEGIN
  CGNV$.nav_opening_wnd := FALSE;
  rg_id := create_group('CGNV$WINDOW_ITEM');
  gc_wnd := add_group_column(rg_id, 'WINDOW', CHAR_COLUMN, 80);
  gc_item := add_group_column(rg_id, 'ITEM', CHAR_COLUMN, 80);
  add_group_row(rg_id, 1);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_wnd, 1, 'CALENDAR');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_item, 1, 'CALENDAR.OK');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 2);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_wnd, 2, 'VENTANA');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_item, 2, 'IVA.EMP_CODIGO');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 3);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_wnd, 3, 'ERRORES');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_item, 3, 'SIS_ERR.BTN_CNC');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 4);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_wnd, 4, 'WINDOW');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_item, 4, 'CGNV$WINDOW_1.BT');
END;

/* CGNV$PRE_FORM_NAVCCF */
  DECLARE
  rg_id RECORDGROUP;
  gc_type GROUPCOLUMN;
  gc_name GROUPCOLUMN;
  gc_parent GROUPCOLUMN;
  gc_tag GROUPCOLUMN;
  gc_extra GROUPCOLUMN;
BEGIN
  CGNV$.nav_close_forms := TRUE;
  CGNV$.nav_opening_wnd := FALSE;
  rg_id := create_group('CGSH$FORM_OBJECTS');
  gc_type := add_group_column(rg_id, 'OBJECT_TYPE', CHAR_COLUMN, 2);
  gc_name := add_group_column(rg_id, 'OBJECT_NAME', CHAR_COLUMN, 40);
  gc_parent := add_group_column(rg_id, 'PARENT_NAME', CHAR_COLUMN, 40);
  gc_tag := add_group_column(rg_id, 'ITEM_TAG', CHAR_COLUMN, 40);
  gc_extra := add_group_column(rg_id, 'EXTRA_TEXT', CHAR_COLUMN, 240);
  add_group_row(rg_id, 1);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_type, 1, 'WN');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_name, 1, 'CALENDAR');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_parent, 1, '');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 2);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_type, 2, 'WN');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_name, 2, 'VENTANA');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_parent, 2, '');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 3);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_type, 3, 'WN');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_name, 3, 'ERRORES');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_parent, 3, '');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 4);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_type, 4, 'WN');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_name, 4, 'WINDOW');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_parent, 4, '');
  add_group_row(rg_id, 5);
  set_group_char_cell(gc_type, 5, 'WN');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_name, 5, 'QMS$HIDDEN_ITEMS');
  set_group_char_cell(gc_parent, 5, '');
END;

/* CGAP$TES_SEQUENCE_BEFORE */
begin
  qms$event_form('WHEN-NEW-FORM-INSTANCE');
/*
 CREADO POR: Juan Carlos Cabrera
 PROPOSITO:  Maximizar la ventana principal y descapacitar el boton de impresión si no tiene
             un reporte asociado
 FECHA:      26/NOV/1999
*/
  SET_WINDOW_PROPERTY(FORMS_MDI_WINDOW,WINDOW_STATE,MAXIMIZE);
  IF :GLOBAL.CG$REPORTE IS NULL THEN
    QMS$TOOLBAR.HIDE_BUTTON('PRINT');
  END IF;
end;

  BEGIN

    WHEN OTHERS THEN
      CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
  END;
END;

BEGIN
   qms$forms_errors.Add_Suppress_Message('FRM-40350');
   GO_BLOCK('IVA');
   EXECUTE_QUERY;
   qms$forms_errors.Delete_Suppress_Message('FRM-40350');
END;

END;

/* CGNV$WHEN_WINDOW_ACTIVATED */
BEGIN
  IF( (:SYSTEM.CURSOR_ITEM IS NOT NULL) AND
      (:SYSTEM.EVENT_WINDOW) !=
       CGNV$GET_ITEM_WINDOW(:SYSTEM.CURSOR_ITEM) ) THEN
    CGNV$.NAVIGATE_TO_WINDOW(:SYSTEM.EVENT_WINDOW);
  END IF;
END;

/* CGFK$QRY_LOOKUP_DATA */
BEGIN
  IF (name_in('IVA.EMP_CODIGO') IS NOT NULL) THEN
    BEGIN
      CGFK$QRY_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK(:IVA.EMAIL ,:IVA.FAX ,:IVA.TELEFONO ,:IVA.NOMBRE_LEGAL ,:IVA.RUC ,:IVA.EMP_CODIGO);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN
        qms$forms_errors.push('La empresa ingresada no existe', 'E', 'OFG', 0);
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
    SET_RECORD_PROPERTY(:SYSTEM.TRIGGER_RECORD, 'IVA', STATUS ,                 QUERY_STATUS);
  END IF;
END;

/* CGFK$RESET_BLOCK_WHERE_CLAUSE */
BEGIN
  IF (CG$SRICNFIVA_GLOBALS.IVA_WHERE <> 'first_time') THEN
    set_block_property('IVA', DEFAULT_WHERE, CG$SRICNFIVA_GLOBALS.IVA_WHERE);
    CG$SRICNFIVA_GLOBALS.IVA_WHERE := 'first_time';
  END IF;
END;

/* CGFK$DEFAULT_WHERE */
BEGIN
  DECLARE
    block_id   Block := find_block('IVA');
    sub_where  VARCHAR2(4000) := NULL;
    def_where  VARCHAR2(4000) := NULL;
    r_string   VARCHAR2(512) := NULL;

    FUNCTION add_and(
      P_WHERE IN VARCHAR2
    ) RETURN VARCHAR2 IS
    BEGIN
      IF (nvl( length(P_WHERE), 0) != 0) THEN
        RETURN( P_WHERE || ' and ');
      ELSE
        RETURN( P_WHERE );
      END IF;
    END;

  BEGIN
    IF ( CG$SRICNFIVA_GLOBALS.IVA_WHERE = 'first_time') THEN
      CG$SRICNFIVA_GLOBALS.IVA_WHERE := get_block_property(block_id, DEFAULT_WHERE);
    END IF;
    def_where := CG$SRICNFIVA_GLOBALS.IVA_WHERE;

    sub_where := NULL;
    r_string := NAME_IN('IVA.RUC');
    IF (r_string IS NOT NULL) THEN
      BEGIN
        IF substr(r_string, 1,1) in ('<','>','=') THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(RUC '|| r_string || ')';
        ELSIF substr(r_string, 1,1) ='#' THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(RUC '|| substr(r_string,2) || ')';
        ELSIF instr(r_string, '') <> 0 THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(RUC like '''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        ELSE
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(RUC ='''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        END IF;
      END;
    END IF;
    r_string := NAME_IN('IVA.NOMBRE_LEGAL');
    IF (r_string IS NOT NULL) THEN
      BEGIN
        IF substr(r_string, 1,1) in ('<','>','=') THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(NOMBRE_LEGAL '|| r_string || ')';
        ELSIF substr(r_string, 1,1) ='#' THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(NOMBRE_LEGAL '|| substr(r_string,2) || ')';
        ELSIF instr(r_string, '') <> 0 THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(NOMBRE_LEGAL like '''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        ELSE
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(NOMBRE_LEGAL ='''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        END IF;
      END;
    END IF;
    r_string := NAME_IN('IVA.TELEFONO');
    IF (r_string IS NOT NULL) THEN
      BEGIN
        IF substr(r_string, 1,1) in ('<','>','=') THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(TELEFONO '|| r_string || ')';
        ELSIF substr(r_string, 1,1) ='#' THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(TELEFONO '|| substr(r_string,2) || ')';
        ELSIF instr(r_string, '') <> 0 THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(TELEFONO like '''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        ELSE
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(TELEFONO ='''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        END IF;
      END;
    END IF;
    r_string := NAME_IN('IVA.FAX');
    IF (r_string IS NOT NULL) THEN
      BEGIN
        IF substr(r_string, 1,1) in ('<','>','=') THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(FAX '|| r_string || ')';
        ELSIF substr(r_string, 1,1) ='#' THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(FAX '|| substr(r_string,2) || ')';
        ELSIF instr(r_string, '') <> 0 THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(FAX like '''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        ELSE
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(FAX ='''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        END IF;
      END;
    END IF;
    r_string := NAME_IN('IVA.EMAIL');
    IF (r_string IS NOT NULL) THEN
      BEGIN
        IF substr(r_string, 1,1) in ('<','>','=') THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(EMAIL '|| r_string || ')';
        ELSIF substr(r_string, 1,1) ='#' THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(EMAIL '|| substr(r_string,2) || ')';
        ELSIF instr(r_string, '') <> 0 THEN
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(EMAIL like '''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        ELSE
          sub_where := add_and( sub_where ) || '(EMAIL ='''|| replace(r_string,'''','''''') || ''')';
        END IF;
      END;
    END IF;
    IF (sub_where IS NOT NULL) THEN
      def_where := add_and( def_where ) || '((EMP_CODIGO) in '||'(select CODIGO '||'from EMPRESAS where '|| sub_where || '))';
    END IF;

    set_block_property(block_id, DEFAULT_WHERE, def_where);

  EXCEPTION
    WHEN VALUE_ERROR THEN
      qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(33, 'Los criterios de consulta son demasiado complejos. Simplifíquelos y vuelva a realizar la consulta.'), 'E', 'OFG', 33);
      qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
  END;
END;
     - Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes
     ^ Execution Hierarchy                           Before
     - Display in 'Keyboard Help'                    No
     - 'Keyboard Help' Text                          
     - Trigger Steps                                 
     ----------
     * Name                                          WHEN-DATABASE-RECORD
     * Subclass Information                          
       ----------
       - Location                                    File
       - Source File                                 
       - Source Path                                 
       - Source Module                               
       - Source Owner                                
       - Source Level                                
       ----------
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     o Trigger Text

BEGIN
-- Cada vez que se crea o se recupera un registros de declaraciones de IVA, se
-- encera el bloque
     GO_BLOCK ('CMPSRI');
     Clear_Block(No_Validate);
     GO_BLOCK ('VNTSRI');
     Clear_Block(No_Validate);
     GO_BLOCK ('IVA');
     SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_COMPRAS',ENABLED,PROPERTY_FALSE);
     SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_VENTAS',ENABLED,PROPERTY_FALSE);
END;

     - Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes
     - Execution Hierarchy                           Override
     - Display in 'Keyboard Help'                    No
     - 'Keyboard Help' Text                          
     - Trigger Steps                                 
     ----------
     * Name                                          ON-ERROR
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text                                  

/* CGTE$BLK_LEVEL_ERROR_TRAP */
BEGIN
  DECLARE
    err_code        CONSTANT NUMBER         := ERROR_CODE;
    err_type        CONSTANT VARCHAR2(3)    := ERROR_TYPE;
    server_err               NUMBER         := abs(DBMS_ERROR_CODE);
    server_msg               VARCHAR2(2000) := DBMS_ERROR_TEXT;
    constraint_name          VARCHAR2(61);
  BEGIN
    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code in (40506, 40508, 40509, 40510) ) THEN

      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      IF ( CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO(server_err, server_msg) ) THEN
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;

      constraint_name := CGTE$STRIP_CONSTRAINT(server_msg);

      IF (server_err = 2291) THEN
        IF (constraint_name = 'IVA_EMP_FK') THEN
          qms$forms_errors.push('La empresa ingresada no existe', 'E', 'OFG', 0);
        ELSE
          qms$forms_errors.push(server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
        END IF;
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;

      IF (server_err = 2292) THEN
        IF (err_code = 40509) THEN
          qms$forms_errors.push(server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
        END IF;
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;
    END IF;

    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code = 40735 ) THEN


      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(server_err)||': '||server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
      qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
    END IF;

    qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(err_code)||': '||ERROR_TEXT, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
    qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;

  END;
END;
     * Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes
     * Execution Hierarchy                           Before
     * Display in 'Keyboard Help'                    Yes
     - 'Keyboard Help' Text                          
     - Trigger Steps                                 
     ----------
     * Name                                          KEY-HELP
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text

    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';

      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);

/* CGFK$WVI_CLR_DEPS_OVF */
BEGIN
  IF (name_in('IVA.EMP_CODIGO') IS NULL) THEN
    IF (:SYSTEM.RECORD_STATUS = 'NEW') THEN
      RETURN;
    END IF;
    BEGIN
      CGSF$CLRLU_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK;
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

/* CGUV$CHK_KEYS_ON_VAL_FLD */
BEGIN
  IF (name_in('IVA.PERIODO') IS NOT NULL OR name_in('IVA.EMP_CODIGO') IS NOT NULL) THEN
  CGUV$CHK_IVA_PK(:IVA.EMP_CODIGO ,:IVA.PERIODO);
  qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(6, 'Ya existe una fila con idéntico <p1>', 'Período,Código' ), 'E', 'OFG', 6);
  qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
  ELSE
      qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(78, 'Debe especificar <p1>', 'Código' ), 'E', 'OFG', 78);
      qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
  END IF;
EXCEPTION
  WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN NULL;
  WHEN OTHERS THEN
    CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
END;

-- Dependiendo del año y mes que se ingrese
-- se asigna el código del período de declaración
BEGIN
DECLARE VPERIODO NUMBER;
BEGIN
   IF :IVA.ANIO IS NOT NULL AND :IVA.MES IS NOT NULL THEN
   BEGIN
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_DEBUG_INFO(TO_CHAR(:IVA.MES)||TO_CHAR(:IVA.ANIO));
      SELECT CODIGO_DESDE+:IVA.MES-1 INTO VPERIODO
      FROM TABLA1
      WHERE ANIO = :IVA.ANIO;
      :IVA.PERIODO := LPAD(TO_CHAR(vPeriodo),3,'0');
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_DEBUG_INFO(:IVA.PERIODO);
   EXCEPTION
   WHEN OTHERS THEN
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00001',TO_CHAR(:IVA.MES),TO_CHAR(:IVA.ANIO)||SQLERRM);
   END;
   END IF;
END;
END;

/* CGAP$OLES_SEQUENCE_BEFORE */
begin
   qms$event_item('WHEN-BUTTON-PRESSED');

BEGIN
   IF :SYSTEM.RECORD_STATUS IN ('QUERY','CHANGED') THEN
      qms$forms_errors.Add_Suppress_Message('FRM-40350');
      GO_BLOCK ('CMPSRI');
      EXECUTE_QUERY;
      GO_BLOCK ('VNTSRI');
      EXECUTE_QUERY;
      qms$forms_errors.Delete_Suppress_Message('FRM-40350');
      IF :IVA.ESTADO_CIERRE = 'F' THEN
        SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_COMPRAS',ENABLED,PROPERTY_TRUE);
        SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_VENTAS',ENABLED,PROPERTY_TRUE);
      ELSE
        SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_COMPRAS',ENABLED,PROPERTY_FALSE);
        SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_VENTAS',ENABLED,PROPERTY_FALSE);
      END IF;
   END IF;
END;

/* CGAP$OLES_SEQUENCE_BEFORE */
begin
   qms$event_item('WHEN-BUTTON-PRESSED');
end;

BEGIN
DECLARE
nNum NUMBER :=0;
-- Genera las compras
BEGIN
IF :IVA.ESTADO_CIERRE = 'V' THEN
   QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00007','Compras');
ELSE
   SELECT COUNT(NUMERO) INTO nNum  --Verifica si existen compras generadas para este periodo
   FROM COMPRAS_NC_ND_SRI
   WHERE IVA_EMP_CODIGO = :IVA.EMP_CODIGO AND
         IVA_PERIODO    = :IVA.PERIODO AND
         SISTEMA_GENERA <> 'SRI';
   IF nNum > 0 THEN
      IF qms$errors.show_Message('CJM-00001','Ya existen Compras registradas para este periodo, desea eliminar los datos','.') THEN
      BEGIN
         SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'BUSY');
         DELETE FROM DETALLES_COMPROBANTES_AFECTADO
         WHERE CMPNCNDSRI_IVA_EMP_CODIGO = :IVA.EMP_CODIGO AND
               CMPNCNDSRI_IVA_PERIODO = :IVA.PERIODO AND
               CMPNCNDSRI_NUMERO IN (SELECT NUMERO
                                     FROM COMPRAS_NC_ND_SRI
                                     WHERE IVA_EMP_CODIGO = :IVA.EMP_CODIGO AND
                                           IVA_PERIODO    = :IVA.PERIODO AND
                                           SISTEMA_GENERA <> 'SRI');
         DELETE FROM COMPRAS_NC_ND_SRI
         WHERE IVA_EMP_CODIGO = :IVA.EMP_CODIGO AND
               IVA_PERIODO    = :IVA.PERIODO AND
               SISTEMA_GENERA <> 'SRI';
         SRIGNRPCK.CONFOMAR_COMPRAS_NC_ND(:IVA.EMP_CODIGO,:IVA.PERIODO,:IVA.MES,:IVA.ANIO);
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00010','Compras');
         SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_ERRORES',ENABLED,PROPERTY_TRUE);
         SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'DEFAULT');
      EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00003',SQLERRM);
      END;
      END IF;
   ELSE
      SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'BUSY');
      SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_ERRORES',ENABLED,PROPERTY_TRUE);
      SRIGNRPCK.CONFOMAR_COMPRAS_NC_ND(:IVA.EMP_CODIGO,:IVA.PERIODO,:IVA.MES,:IVA.ANIO);
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00010','Compras');
      SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'DEFAULT');
   END IF;
END IF;
END;
END;
       - Fire in Enter-Query Mode                    Yes
       o Execution Hierarchy                         Override
       - Display in 'Keyboard Help'                  No
       - 'Keyboard Help' Text                        
       - Trigger Steps                               
       ----------

/* CGAP$OLES_SEQUENCE_BEFORE */
begin
   qms$event_item('WHEN-BUTTON-PRESSED');
end;

BEGIN
DECLARE
nNum NUMBER :=0;
-- Genera las compras
BEGIN
IF :IVA.ESTADO_CIERRE = 'V' THEN
   QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00007','Ventas');
ELSE
   SELECT COUNT(NUMERO) INTO nNum
   FROM VENTAS_NC_ND_SRI
   WHERE IVA_EMP_CODIGO = :IVA.EMP_CODIGO AND
         IVA_PERIODO    = :IVA.PERIODO AND
         SISTEMA_GENERA <> 'SRI';
   IF nNum > 0 THEN
      IF qms$errors.show_Message('CJM-00001','Ya existen Ventas registradas para este periodo, desea eliminar los datos','.') THEN
      BEGIN
         SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'BUSY');
         DELETE FROM VENTAS_NC_ND_SRI
         WHERE IVA_EMP_CODIGO = :IVA.EMP_CODIGO AND
               IVA_PERIODO    = :IVA.PERIODO AND
               SISTEMA_GENERA <> 'SRI';
         SRIGNRPCK.CONFORMAR_VENTAS_NC_ND(:IVA.EMP_CODIGO,:IVA.PERIODO,:IVA.MES,:IVA.ANIO);
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00010','Ventas');
         SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_ERRORES',ENABLED,PROPERTY_TRUE);
         SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'DEFAULT');
      EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00003',SQLERRM);
      END;
      END IF;
   ELSE
      SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'BUSY');
      SET_ITEM_PROPERTY('BTN_ERRORES',ENABLED,PROPERTY_TRUE);
      SRIGNRPCK.CONFORMAR_VENTAS_NC_ND(:IVA.EMP_CODIGO,:IVA.PERIODO,:IVA.MES,:IVA.ANIO);
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00010','Ventas');
      SET_APPLICATION_PROPERTY(CURSOR_STYLE,'DEFAULT');
   END IF;
END IF;
END;
END;

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

     - Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes

     ----------
     * Name                                          ON-ERROR
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text                                  

/* CGTE$BLK_LEVEL_ERROR_TRAP */
BEGIN
  DECLARE
    err_code        CONSTANT NUMBER         := ERROR_CODE;
    err_type        CONSTANT VARCHAR2(3)    := ERROR_TYPE;
    server_err               NUMBER         := abs(DBMS_ERROR_CODE);
    server_msg               VARCHAR2(2000) := DBMS_ERROR_TEXT;
    constraint_name          VARCHAR2(61);
  BEGIN
    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code in (40506, 40508, 40509, 40510) ) THEN

      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      IF ( CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO(server_err, server_msg) ) THEN
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;

      constraint_name := CGTE$STRIP_CONSTRAINT(server_msg);

    END IF;

    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code = 40735 ) THEN


      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(server_err)||': '||server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
      qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
    END IF;

    qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(err_code)||': '||ERROR_TEXT, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
    qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;

  END;
END;
     * Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes
     * Execution Hierarchy                           Before

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';

      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);

      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;

    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';

        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;

  END IF;

        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;

     ----------
     * Name                                          ON-ERROR
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text                                  

/* CGTE$BLK_LEVEL_ERROR_TRAP */
BEGIN
  DECLARE
    err_code        CONSTANT NUMBER         := ERROR_CODE;
    err_type        CONSTANT VARCHAR2(3)    := ERROR_TYPE;
    server_err               NUMBER         := abs(DBMS_ERROR_CODE);
    server_msg               VARCHAR2(2000) := DBMS_ERROR_TEXT;
    constraint_name          VARCHAR2(61);
  BEGIN
    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code in (40506, 40508, 40509, 40510) ) THEN

      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      IF ( CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO(server_err, server_msg) ) THEN
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;

      constraint_name := CGTE$STRIP_CONSTRAINT(server_msg);

    END IF;

    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code = 40735 ) THEN


      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(server_err)||': '||server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
      qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
    END IF;

    qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(err_code)||': '||ERROR_TEXT, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
    qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;

  END;
END;
     * Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes
     * Execution Hierarchy                           Before
     * Display in 'Keyboard Help'                    Yes
     - 'Keyboard Help' Text                          
     - Trigger Steps                                 
     ----------
     * Name                                          KEY-HELP
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

     - Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes

     - 'Keyboard Help' Text                          
     - Trigger Steps                                 
     ----------
     * Name                                          ON-ERROR
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text                                  

/* CGTE$BLK_LEVEL_ERROR_TRAP */
BEGIN
  DECLARE
    err_code        CONSTANT NUMBER         := ERROR_CODE;
    err_type        CONSTANT VARCHAR2(3)    := ERROR_TYPE;
    server_err               NUMBER         := abs(DBMS_ERROR_CODE);
    server_msg               VARCHAR2(2000) := DBMS_ERROR_TEXT;
    constraint_name          VARCHAR2(61);
  BEGIN
    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code in (40506, 40508, 40509, 40510) ) THEN

      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      IF ( CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO(server_err, server_msg) ) THEN
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;

      constraint_name := CGTE$STRIP_CONSTRAINT(server_msg);

      IF (server_err = 2291) THEN
        qms$forms_errors.push(server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;

      IF (server_err = 2292) THEN
        IF (err_code = 40509) THEN
          qms$forms_errors.push(server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
        END IF;
        QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.RAISE_FAILURE;
      END IF;
    END IF;

    IF (err_type = 'FRM' and
        err_code = 40735 ) THEN


      WHILE (server_err = 604) LOOP
        CGTE$POP_ERROR_STACK(server_err, server_msg);
      END LOOP;

      qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(server_err)||': '||server_msg, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
      qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;
    END IF;

    qms$forms_errors.push(err_type||'-'||to_char(err_code)||': '||ERROR_TEXT, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
    qms$forms_errors.raise_failure;

  END;
END;
     * Fire in Enter-Query Mode                      Yes
     * Execution Hierarchy                           Before
     * Display in 'Keyboard Help'                    Yes
     - 'Keyboard Help' Text                          
     - Trigger Steps                                 
     ----------
     * Name                                          KEY-HELP
     - Subclass Information                          
     - Comments                                      
     - Trigger Style                                 PL/SQL
     * Trigger Text

/* CGHP$CALL_HELP_FORM */
BEGIN
  :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := '';
  IF (:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE IS NULL) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(23, 'Falta el fichero de ayuda o es incorrecto'), 'W', 'OFG', 23);
  ELSE
    :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE := :GLOBAL.CG$HP_HPATH || '';
    BEGIN
      CGHP$CALL_MS_HELP(0 ,:GLOBAL.CG$HP_HFILE);
    EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
        CGTE$OTHER_EXCEPTIONS;
    END;
  END IF;
END;

BEGIN
-- Fija los parámetros sesion,empresa y destino para imprimir los errores
DECLARE
   pl_id ParamList;
BEGIN
   pl_id := Get_Parameter_List('PARAMETRO');
   IF NOT Id_Null(pl_id) THEN
      Destroy_Parameter_List( pl_id );
   END IF;
   pl_id := Create_Parameter_List('PARAMETRO');
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'PSESION',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.SESION);
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'PNOMBREEMPRESA',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.CG$NOMBRE_EMPRESA);
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'PARAMFORM',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.RPT_PRM_FRM);
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'DESTYPE',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.RPT_DESTINO);
   Run_Product(REPORTS, 'ADMRPTERR', SYNCHRONOUS, RUNTIME,FILESYSTEM, pl_id, NULL);
END;
END;

BEGIN
-- Fija los parámetros sesion,empresa y destino para imprimir los errores
DECLARE
   pl_id ParamList;
BEGIN
   pl_id := Get_Parameter_List('PARAMETRO');
   IF NOT Id_Null(pl_id) THEN
      Destroy_Parameter_List( pl_id );
   END IF;
   pl_id := Create_Parameter_List('PARAMETRO');
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'PSESION',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.SESION);
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'PNOMBREEMPRESA',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.CG$NOMBRE_EMPRESA);
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'PARAMFORM',TEXT_PARAMETER,:GLOBAL.RPT_PRM_FRM);
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'DESTYPE',TEXT_PARAMETER,'File');
   Add_Parameter(pl_id,'DESFORMAT',TEXT_PARAMETER,'html');
   IF :SIS_ERR.ARCHIVO IS NULL THEN
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('Debe ingresar el nombre del archivo');
   ELSE
      Add_Parameter(pl_id,'DESNAME',TEXT_PARAMETER,RTRIM(:SIS_ERR.ARCHIVO)||'.html');
      Run_Product(REPORTS, 'ADMRPTERR', SYNCHRONOUS, RUNTIME,FILESYSTEM, pl_id, NULL);
   END IF;
END;
END;

Revision When       Who
         What
5.0      25-06-1998 S. Davelaar
         Headstart Template Package 5.0 BETA
5.0.1    18-08-1998 S. Davelaar
         - QMSSO$CONCEAL_ITEM added
         - CGSO$CANVAS_SPREAD now subclasses from CGSO$CANVAS_POPUP
         - QMSSO$MODAL_DOCUMENT_WINDOW added
         - parameter QMS$MENU_CALLING_FORM removed
         - triggers KEY-CLRFRM, PRE-FORM, QUERY_FIND, WHEN-NEW_BLOCK-INSTANCE,
           and WHEN-NEW-FORM-INSTANCE moved from object group QMS$STND_MODULE
           to object group QMS$MODULE
         - Lov QMS$ENABLED_LIST_LAMP changed to Record Group LOV
         - Record group QMS$ENABLE_LIST_LAMP added to object group QMS$MODULE
         - CG$LOV added (will be renamed to CGSO$LOV if OFG bug causing wrong
           LOV height to be generatedif CGSO$LOV is present, is fixed)
         - Background item VA's no longer inherit from qms$item_font (now using
           <Unspecified> setting)
         - Foreground prompt VA's no longer inherit from qms$prompt_font (now
           using <Unspecified> setting)
         - Visual attribute QMS$BOLD added
         - Visual attribute qms$gui_item_font added
         - item qms$block_info made non-navigable, and disabled
         - WHEN-WINDOW-CLOSED trigger added to QMSSO$MODULE
         - Iconic Calendar buttons now subclass QMSSO$CALENDAR_BUTTON,
           tooltips added
         - KEY-EXIT trigger added to QMSSO$MODULE
         - QMSSO$QUERY_ONLY_ITEM added
         - width and height of CGSO$WINDOW set to 1
         - Tooltip VA of QMSSO$TOOLBAR_BUTTON set to QMS$TOOLTIP
         - Fire in enter-query mode property switched on for
           WHEN-NEW-RECORD-INSTANCE trigger in QMSSO$MSEL_BLOCK (now required
           for highlighting queryable items)
         - QMSSO$NO_BEVEL_ITEM added
5.0.2    24-09-1998 S. Davelaar
         - Form level PRE-BLOCK trigger removed
         - PRE-BLOCK trigger added to CGSO$BLOCK
         - PRE-BLOCK trigger added to CGSO$BLOCK_CT
         - qms$block_info item made non-queryable, number of items displayed
           set to 1
         - QMSSO$WIZARD_BLOCK: Database Block property set to Yes
         - CONSOLE_WINDOW renamed to QMS$HIDDEN_ITEMS
         - QMSSO$TOOLBAR_WINDOW renamed to QMSSO$WEB_TOOLBAR_WINDOW
         - KEY-DOWN, KEY-UP, KEY-PRVREC, KEY-NXTREC, KEY-NXTREC added to
           QMSSO$MSEL_BLOCK
         - KEY-MENU added to QMSSO$MODULE
         - Query length set to 500 in CGSO$DEFAULT_ITEM
         - WHEN-BUTTON-PRESSED trigger now owned by all QMSSO buttons individually,
           instead of inherited with the trigger text being overridden
         - Default value of parameter SWITCH_MENU set to DO_REPLACE
         - Renamed all icons in toolbar, calendar and CGSO$LOV_BUT to have qms prefix
         - KEY-EXIT trigger moved from object group QMSSO$MODULE to QMSSO$STND_MODULE
5.0.3    03-12-1998 S. Davelaar
         - Item CGSO$DATE: maximum length changed to 11
         - Added CGSO$DATETIME subclasses CGSO$DATE overriding datatype (set to
           datetime), and maximum length (set to 20)
         - Item QMSSO$TEXT: maximum length and query length set to 2000,
           Multi-line set to Yes
         - Item CGSO$DEFAULT_ITEM: maximum length and query length set to 2000
5.0.3.1  14-01-1999 S. Davelaar
         - Parameter qmsolb50_revision renamed to objlib_revision, parameter
           objlib_name added and stored in object group QMSSO$MODULE
         - Object group QMSSO$MODULE: QMS$BLUE_FOREGROUND
         - Object group QMSSO$MODULE: Trigger KEY-HELP added
         - Object group QMSSO$MODULE: Paremeter SCHEMA_OWNER added
         - Block CGSO$BLOCK: POST-SELECT trigger added as work around for OFG
           bug 818001
         - Block CGSO$BLOCK_CT: Property query all records set to True
         - Block QMSSO$DYNAMIC_PROMPT_VALUE removed
         - Block QMSSO$WIZARD: item wizard_height added
         - Block QMSSO$WIZARD_SPLIT_BLOCK added, subclasses QMSSO$WIZARD, two
           own triggers added: ON-LOCK and WHEN-VALIDATE-RECORD
         - Visual Attribute QMS$BLUE_FOREGROUND added
         - Visual Attribute CALENDAR DISABLED: background color changed to gray
         - Visual Attribute QMS$PROMPT_LIGHT_BLUE renamed to QMS$PROMPT_LIGHTBLUE
         - Item QMSSO$TEXT: Trigger WHEN-NEW-ITEM-INSTANCE added
         - Item QMSSO$BLUE_TEXT added
         - Item QMSSO$BLUE_BOLD_TEXT: current record VA set to
           QMS$BLUE_FOREGROUND, subclasses from QMSSO$BLUE_TEXT
           trigger WHEN-TAB-PAGE-CHANGED removed
         - Item QMSSO$DISABLED_BUTTON added.
         - Tooltip property of item qms$block_info cleared in all blocks except
           QMSSO$BLOCK_MSEL
         - Items CALENDAR.OK and CALENDAR.CANCEL: Mouse navigate property set to True
         - Item CGSO$DEFAULT_ITEM: when-mouse-click trigger removed
         - Item CGSO$DEFAULT_ITEM: Tooltip text set to 'No hint available.'
           (Work around for webforms bug, to be able to show tooltips on WEB)
         - All QMSSO$ buttons: calls to qms$event_item removed from WHEN-BUTTON-
           PRESSED triggers
         - New source item QMSSO$LOV_FORM_ITEM
         - Window QMSSO$DIALOG_WINDOW: Inherit menu property set to No
         - Window CALENDAR: Inherit menu property set to No
         - Popup Menu Item HELP_CONTEXT: PL/SQL code re-inherited from parent
         - Block QMS$TOOLBAR: WHEN-BUTTON-PRESSED changed into WHEN-MOUSE-CLICK
           trigger to be able to trap right-mouse-button click (forms bug 636000)
         - Block QMS$TOOLBAR: ORDER_BY poplist added with WHEN-LIST-CHANGED trigger.

     ^ Command Type                                  Null
     - Visible                                       Yes
     ^ Hint                                          Corta la selección actual y la pone en el apuntador
     ^ Help Description                              Removes the selected text and places it on the clipboard.  The contents of the clipboard can be pasted into text items or into other applications.  The contents of the clipboard are overwritten each time a Copy or Cut is performed.

The Copy and Cut commands are disabled when no text is selected.  The Cut command is also disabled if the current item is not updatable.

       ----------

     ^ Label                                         Lista de &Valores...
     ^ Menu Item Type                                Plain
     ^ Magic Item                                    None
     ^ Command Type                                  PL/SQL
     - Menu Item Code                                

qms$menu.set_current_action('LIST');
execute_trigger('QMS$MENU_ITEM');
     - Visible                                       Yes
     ^ Hint                                          Invoca una ventana con una lista de valores valida desde la cual escoger
     ^ Help Description                              Displays a list of values (LOV) which is a scrollable pop-up window that provides you with a selection list containing one or more columns with all the valid values available for the current text item.  The LOV appears in a modal window which means you cannot work in other windows when an LOV is displayed.  You can move and resize the LOV (if the runtime window manager supports doing so).  The LOV window remains displayed until you select a single value or cancel the LOV.

Use the [Up] and [Down] keys or the scroll bar to navigate through the list.  Press the OK button or the [Accept] key to choose the selected value and close the list of values window.  Press the Cancel button to leave the list without making a selection.  When you select a value, the value is automatically returned into the current item.  Using an LOV can save keystrokes during data-entry and it ensures that the value entered is valid for that item.

There are LOV auto-reduction and search features to help you locate a value in a list.  To use auto-reduction, simply type the desired entry directly in the list pane of the LOV window.  As each character is entered, the list is reduced to only those values that match the string being entered.  Pressing [Delete Backwards] expands the reduced list of choices.  Auto-reduction works by comparing the string you entered with the values in the first column displayed in the LOV.  

You can use the search feature to locate a match for a specific text string and to do wildcard searches using "" and "_".  To use the search feature, enter your search criteria string in the LOV's Find field and press the Find button to execute the search.  The list is shortened to those choices whose first column values match your search criteria.  Note that if you precede the search criteria with a "" symbol, the search will be performed using all the LOV columns.

There is also an automatic search and complete feature that may have been implemented by the form designer.  An LOV evaluates a text item's current value as a search value.  That is, if you invoke the list of values in a text item and the item already contains a value, that value is automatically used as if you had entered it into the LOV's find field to reduce the list.  If the value would reduce the list to match only one record, the LOV does not display, but automatically enters the complete value into the current item.

For date or datetime fields, a calendar window is invoked which provides easy navigation between dates, months and years and allows you to quickly enter a date (and time for datetime fields).  Calendar windows help to ensure that you enter valid dates in the correct format.  The calendar window appears showing the same month as the current date in the date field with the date highlighted.  If no date exists in the date field, the calendar displays the current month with today's date highlighted.  Today's date is also underlined.  If there is a range of dates that is not valid for this field then the form designer can disable the dates on the calendar.

To help identify when an LOV is available for an item, a "<LIST>" (or "List of Values") lamp is displayed on the status line when you navigate into the item.

This function is also available through a button on the toolbar or directly adjacent the item.


For more information about runtime item interaction and examples, see the Oracle Forms Reference manual or the Getting Started with Forms manual.

     - Visible                                       Yes
     ^ Hint                                          Entra en modo de ayuda contextual
     ^ Help Description                              Switches the mouse pointer to a question mark "?", setting the application in help mode.  You can then click on any menu entry, button or item to get context-sensitive help.  A pop-up window will appear containing an explanation of the object.

This function is also available via the iconic help button on the toolbar.

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGFK$QRY_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGFK$QRY_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK */
PROCEDURE CGFK$QRY_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK(
   P_EMAIL        IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_FAX          IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_TELEFONO     IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_NOMBRE_LEGAL IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_RUC          IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_EMP_CODIGO   IN     VARCHAR2) IS
BEGIN
  DECLARE
    CURSOR C IS
      select EMP.RUC
            ,EMP.NOMBRE_LEGAL
            ,EMP.TELEFONO
            ,EMP.FAX
            ,EMP.EMAIL
      from   EMPRESAS EMP
      where  EMP.CODIGO = P_EMP_CODIGO;
  BEGIN
    OPEN C;
    FETCH C
    into    P_RUC
          , P_NOMBRE_LEGAL
          , P_TELEFONO
          , P_FAX
          , P_EMAIL;
    IF COTFOUND THEN
      CLOSE C;
      RAISE NO_DATA_FOUND;
    END IF;
    CLOSE C;
  END;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   - Subclass Information

/* CGSF$CLRLU_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK */
PROCEDURE CGSF$CLRLU_IVA_IVA_EMP_FK IS
BEGIN
  IF (:IVA.EMP_CODIGO IS NOT NULL) THEN
    :IVA.EMP_CODIGO := NULL;
  END IF;
  IF (:IVA.RUC IS NOT NULL) THEN
    :IVA.RUC := NULL;
  END IF;
  IF (:IVA.NOMBRE_LEGAL IS NOT NULL) THEN
    :IVA.NOMBRE_LEGAL := NULL;
  END IF;
  IF (:IVA.TELEFONO IS NOT NULL) THEN
    :IVA.TELEFONO := NULL;
  END IF;
  IF (:IVA.FAX IS NOT NULL) THEN
    :IVA.FAX := NULL;
  END IF;
  IF (:IVA.EMAIL IS NOT NULL) THEN
    :IVA.EMAIL := NULL;
  END IF;
END;

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGUV$CHK_IVA_PK
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGUV$CHK_IVA_PK */
PROCEDURE CGUV$CHK_IVA_PK(
   P_EMP_CODIGO IN VARCHAR2
  ,P_PERIODO    IN VARCHAR2) IS
  CG$DUMMY VARCHAR2(1);
BEGIN
    DECLARE
      CURSOR C IS
        select  '1'
        from    IVA
        where   PERIODO = P_PERIODO
        and     EMP_CODIGO = P_EMP_CODIGO;
    BEGIN
      OPEN C;
      FETCH C
      into    CG$DUMMY;
      IF COTFOUND THEN
        CLOSE C;
        RAISE NO_DATA_FOUND;
      END IF;
      CLOSE C;
    END;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO */
FUNCTION CGTE$CHECK_CONSTRAINT_VIO(
   P_SERVER_ERR IN NUMBER
  ,P_SERVER_MSG IN VARCHAR2)
RETURN BOOLEAN IS
  constraint_name VARCHAR2(61);  /* Violated constraint */
BEGIN
  IF ( not (P_SERVER_ERR in  (1, 2290) OR
           (P_SERVER_ERR >= 20000 AND P_SERVER_ERR <= 20999) ) )
  THEN
    RETURN( FALSE );
  END IF;

  IF (P_SERVER_ERR >= 20000 AND P_SERVER_ERR <= 20999) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(''||CGTE$STRIP_FIRST_ERROR(P_SERVER_MSG), 'E', 'OFG', 0);
    RETURN( TRUE );
  END IF;

  constraint_name := CGTE$STRIP_CONSTRAINT(P_SERVER_MSG);
  IF (P_SERVER_ERR = 1) THEN
    IF (constraint_name = 'IVA_PK') THEN
      qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(6, 'Ya existe una fila con idéntico <p1>', 'Período,Código' ), 'E', 'OFG', 6);
    ELSIF (constraint_name = 'EMP_PK') THEN
      qms$forms_errors.push('Código de empresa ya existente', 'E', 'OFG', 0);
    ELSIF (constraint_name = 'ERR_PK') THEN
      qms$forms_errors.push(QMS$FORMS_ERRORS.MSGGETTEXT(6, 'Ya existe una fila con idéntico <p1>', '' ), 'E', 'OFG', 6);
    ELSE
      qms$forms_errors.push(P_SERVER_MSG, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
    END IF;
  ELSIF (P_SERVER_ERR = 2290) THEN
    qms$forms_errors.push(P_SERVER_MSG, 'I', 'OFG', 0);
  END IF;
  RETURN( TRUE );
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8394 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGLY$DISPLAY_CANVASES
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGLY$DISPLAY_CANVASES */
PROCEDURE CGLY$DISPLAY_CANVASES(
   P_CANVAS_LIST    IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_CURRENT_CANVAS IN     VARCHAR2
  ,P_BASE_CANVAS    IN     VARCHAR2) IS
  canvas_list VARCHAR2(255);  /* List of displayed canvases */
  canvas_to_raise VARCHAR2(255);  /* Canvas to raise to the top */
BEGIN
  IF ( P_CURRENT_CANVAS = P_BASE_CANVAS) THEN
    P_CANVAS_LIST := P_CURRENT_CANVAS || ',';
  ELSE
    P_CANVAS_LIST := replace(P_CANVAS_LIST, P_CURRENT_CANVAS || ',');
    IF ( get_view_property(P_BASE_CANVAS, VISIBLE) = 'FALSE') THEN
      canvas_list := P_CANVAS_LIST;
      WHILE (canvas_list IS NOT NULL) LOOP
        canvas_to_raise := substr(canvas_list, 1, instr(canvas_list, ','));
        canvas_list := replace(canvas_list, canvas_to_raise);
        CGLY$RAISE_CANVAS(rtrim(canvas_to_raise, ','));
      END LOOP;
    END IF;
    P_CANVAS_LIST := P_CANVAS_LIST || P_CURRENT_CANVAS || ',';
  END IF;
  CGLY$RAISE_CANVAS(P_CURRENT_CANVAS);
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGLY$GET_RELATED_CANVASES
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGLY$GET_RELATED_CANVASES */
PROCEDURE CGLY$GET_RELATED_CANVASES(
   P_CURRENT_CANVAS IN OUT VARCHAR2
  ,P_BASE_CANVAS    IN OUT VARCHAR2) IS
BEGIN
  IF ( P_CURRENT_CANVAS = 'CG$SPREAD_TABLE_2') THEN
    P_CURRENT_CANVAS := 'CG$PAGE_1';
  ELSIF ( P_CURRENT_CANVAS = 'CG$SPREAD_TABLE_1') THEN
    P_CURRENT_CANVAS := 'CG$PAGE_1';
  END IF;
  /* CFLT */
  P_BASE_CANVAS := P_CURRENT_CANVAS;
  IF (get_view_property(P_CURRENT_CANVAS, WINDOW_NAME) = 'CALENDAR') THEN
    :CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWCALENDAR_PAGE := P_BASE_CANVAS;
  ELSIF (get_view_property(P_CURRENT_CANVAS, WINDOW_NAME) = 'VENTANA') THEN
    IF (:CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWVENTANA_PAGE IS NULL OR :CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWVENTANA_PAGE != P_BASE_CANVAS) THEN
      set_view_property('CG$SPREAD_TABLE_2', VISIBLE, PROPERTY_OFF);
      set_view_property('CG$SPREAD_TABLE_1', VISIBLE, PROPERTY_OFF);
    END IF;
    :CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWVENTANA_PAGE := P_BASE_CANVAS;
  ELSIF (get_view_property(P_CURRENT_CANVAS, WINDOW_NAME) = 'ERRORES') THEN
    :CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWERRORES_PAGE := P_BASE_CANVAS;
  ELSIF (get_view_property(P_CURRENT_CANVAS, WINDOW_NAME) = 'WINDOW') THEN
    :CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWWINDOW_PAGE := P_BASE_CANVAS;
  ELSIF (get_view_property(P_CURRENT_CANVAS, WINDOW_NAME) = 'QMS$HIDDEN_ITEMS') THEN
    :CG$CTRL.CG$WINDOWQMS$HIDDEN_ITEMS_PAGE := P_BASE_CANVAS;
  END IF;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGLY$RAISE_CANVAS
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGLY$RAISE_CANVAS */
PROCEDURE CGLY$RAISE_CANVAS(
   P_CANVAS IN VARCHAR2) IS
BEGIN
  set_view_property(P_CANVAS, VISIBLE, PROPERTY_ON);
  IF ( P_CANVAS = 'CG$PAGE_1') THEN
    set_view_property('CG$SPREAD_TABLE_2', VISIBLE, PROPERTY_ON);
    set_view_property('CG$SPREAD_TABLE_1', VISIBLE, PROPERTY_ON);
  END IF;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGLY$CANVAS_MANAGEMENT
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGLY$CANVAS_MANAGEMENT */
PROCEDURE CGLY$CANVAS_MANAGEMENT IS
  current_canvas VARCHAR2(61) := get_item_property(:SYSTEM.CURSOR_ITEM, ITEM_CANVAS);
  base_canvas VARCHAR2(61);
  canvas_list VARCHAR2(255);
BEGIN
  IF ( (:CG$CTRL.CG$LAST_CANVAS IS NULL) OR (:CG$CTRL.CG$LAST_CANVAS != current_canvas) ) THEN
    :CG$CTRL.CG$LAST_CANVAS := current_canvas;
    set_window_property( get_view_property( current_canvas, WINDOW_NAME ), VISIBLE, PROPERTY_ON);
    CGLY$GET_RELATED_CANVASES(current_canvas, base_canvas);
    IF ( base_canvas = 'CG$PAGE_1') THEN
      canvas_list := :CG$CTRL.CG$PAGE_1_LIST;
    ELSIF ( base_canvas = 'CG$PAGE_2') THEN
      canvas_list := :CG$CTRL.CG$PAGE_2_LIST;
    ELSIF ( base_canvas = 'CG$PAGE_3') THEN
      canvas_list := :CG$CTRL.CG$PAGE_3_LIST;
    END IF;
    CGLY$DISPLAY_CANVASES(canvas_list, current_canvas, base_canvas);
    IF ( base_canvas = 'CG$PAGE_1') THEN
      :CG$CTRL.CG$PAGE_1_LIST := canvas_list;
    ELSIF ( base_canvas = 'CG$PAGE_2') THEN
      :CG$CTRL.CG$PAGE_2_LIST := canvas_list;
    ELSIF ( base_canvas = 'CG$PAGE_3') THEN
      :CG$CTRL.CG$PAGE_3_LIST := canvas_list;
    END IF;
  END IF;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            CGNV$PREV_ITEM
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

/* CGNV$PREV_ITEM */
PROCEDURE CGNV$PREV_ITEM IS
  cur_itm VARCHAR2(80);
  cur_blk VARCHAR2(80);
  fst_itm VARCHAR2(80);
BEGIN
  cur_itm :=  :SYSTEM.CURSOR_ITEM;
  cur_blk :=  :SYSTEM.CURSOR_BLOCK;
  fst_itm :=  CGNV$FIRST_NAV_ITEM(cur_blk);
  IF ((cur_itm = fst_itm) AND
       (get_block_property(cur_blk, NAVIGATION_STYLE)
        ='CHANGE_RECORD') AND
       (get_block_property(cur_blk, CURRENT_RECORD) = 1)) THEN
    set_block_property(cur_blk, NAVIGATION_STYLE, CHANGE_BLOCK);
    previous_item;
    set_block_property(cur_blk, NAVIGATION_STYLE, CHANGE_RECORD);
  ELSE
    previous_item;
  END IF;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            MOSTRAR_ERRORES
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

PROCEDURE Mostrar_Errores IS
--Presenta el bloque de errores de contabilización
BEGIN
  qms$forms_errors.Add_Suppress_Message ('FRM-40350');
  GO_BLOCK('SIS_ERR');
  EXECUTE_QUERY;
  qms$forms_errors.Delete_Suppress_Message ('FRM-40350');
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            COMPLETAR_DATOS_VENTAS
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

PROCEDURE COMPLETAR_DATOS_VENTAS IS
--Recupera los datos de compras que no están en la vista COMPRAS_SRI
VALIDADOR NUMBER;
BEGIN
   IF :VNTSRI.NRO_ID_DOCUMENTO IS NOT NULL THEN
      VALIDADOR :=GNRL.Validar_Ruc_Y_Cedula(:VNTSRI.NRO_ID_DOCUMENTO,'VT',:VNTSRI.CODIGO_TIPO_COMPROBANTE,'M');
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_DEBUG_INFO('El código es: '||TO_CHAR(VALIDADOR));
--      IF validador > 0 AND :VNTSRI.NRO_ID_DOCUMENTO NOT IN ('9999999999999','0000000000001') THEN
        :VNTSRI.CODIGO_TRN := LPAD(TO_CHAR(VALIDADOR),2,'0');
--      END IF;
   END IF;
   IF :VNTSRI.FECHA IS NOT NULL AND :VNTSRI.CODIGO_TIPO_COMPROBANTE IS NOT NULL THEN
      BEGIN
         SELECT DESCRIPCION INTO :VNTSRI.TIPO_COMPROBANTE
         FROM TABLAS_DE_REFERENCIAS
         WHERE CODIGO_TABLA = 'TABLA3' AND
               CODIGO = :VNTSRI.CODIGO_TIPO_COMPROBANTE;
      EXCEPTION
      WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00002','Tipo de Comprobante');
      END;
      BEGIN
         SELECT CODIGO INTO :VNTSRI.CODIGO_IVA
         FROM TABLAS_DE_REFERENCIAS
         WHERE CODIGO_TABLA = 'TABLA5' AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_DESDE <= :VNTSRI.FECHA AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_HASTA IS NOT NULL AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_HASTA>= :VNTSRI.FECHA;
      EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
      BEGIN
         SELECT CODIGO INTO :VNTSRI.CODIGO_IVA
         FROM TABLAS_DE_REFERENCIAS
         WHERE CODIGO_TABLA = 'TABLA5' AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_DESDE <= :VNTSRI.FECHA AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_HASTA IS NULL;
      EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00002','Porcentaje de IVA');
      END;
      END;
   END IF;
END;
   - Program Unit Type                               Message 8393 not found;  product=forms50; facility=FMD

   ----------
   * Name                                            COMPLETAR_DATOS_COMPRAS
   - Subclass Information                            
   - Comments                                        
   * Program Unit Text                               

PROCEDURE COMPLETAR_DATOS_COMPRAS IS
--Recupera los datos de compras que no están en la vista COMPRAS_SRI
VALIDADOR NUMBER;
BEGIN
   IF :CMPSRI.NRO_ID_DOCUMENTO IS NOT NULL THEN
      VALIDADOR :=GNRL.Validar_Ruc_Y_Cedula(:CMPSRI.NRO_ID_DOCUMENTO,'TL',:CMPSRI.CODIGO_TIPO_COMPROBANTE,'M');
      QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_DEBUG_INFO('El código es: '||TO_CHAR(VALIDADOR));
      IF validador > 0 THEN
        :CMPSRI.CODIGO_TRN := LPAD(TO_CHAR(VALIDADOR),2,'0');
      END IF;
   END IF;
   IF :CMPSRI.FECHA_EMISION IS NOT NULL AND:CMPSRI.CODIGO_TIPO_COMPROBANTE IS NOT NULL THEN
      BEGIN
         SELECT DESCRIPCION INTO :CMPSRI.TIPO_COMPROBANTE
         FROM TABLAS_DE_REFERENCIAS
         WHERE CODIGO_TABLA = 'TABLA3' AND
               CODIGO = :CMPSRI.CODIGO_TIPO_COMPROBANTE;
      EXCEPTION
      WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00002','Tipo de Comprobante');
      END;
      BEGIN
         SELECT CODIGO INTO :CMPSRI.CODIGO_IVA
         FROM TABLAS_DE_REFERENCIAS
         WHERE CODIGO_TABLA = 'TABLA5' AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_DESDE <= :CMPSRI.FECHA_EMISION AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_HASTA IS NOT NULL AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_HASTA>= :CMPSRI.FECHA_EMISION;
      EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
      BEGIN
         SELECT CODIGO INTO :CMPSRI.CODIGO_IVA
         FROM TABLAS_DE_REFERENCIAS
         WHERE CODIGO_TABLA = 'TABLA5' AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_DESDE <= :CMPSRI.FECHA_EMISION AND
               FECHA_VALIDEZ_HASTA IS NULL;
      EXCEPTION
      WHEN OTHERS THEN
         QMS$ERRORS.SHOW_MESSAGE('SRI-00002','Porcentaje de IVA');
      END;
      END;
   END IF;
END;

   - Record Group Type                               Query
   * Record Group Query                              select  substr(RV_LOW_VALUE,1,1)  RV_LOW_VALUE
      , substr(RV_MEANING,1,9)  RV_MEANING
      , substr(RV_ABBREVIATION,1,2)  RV_ABBREVIATION
from    CG_REF_CODES
where   RV_DOMAIN = 'LOGICO'
order by  RV_LOW_VALUE
